{
  "text": "The notion of wave that we use is a little bit different to the one introduced by Dalla Preda, Giacobazzi and Debray [CITATION_1] (called phase). The main advantage of our approach is that waves can be computed on the fly. In particular, as the experiments showed it, we could recognize the hooking of the OpenProcess kernel function at run time.",
